parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the strut tower can cause the vehicle to become difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: Noise coming from the front wheel area
grinding noise when turning
strut housing tearing away from the frame
brake lines damaged
and loss of brake fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm bushing can cause the vehicle to sway or wobble while driving, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or wobbles while driving
especially at higher speeds
and uneven road surfaces or bumps can trigger the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear control arm can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or wobbles while driving
especially at higher speeds
and uneven road surfaces or bumps can trigger the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become structurally unsound, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
especially on the strut tower and control arm areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag to deploy in the event of an accident can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Air bag did not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Strut Housing Corrosion and Steering Column Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the strut housing and steering column can cause the loss of steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
grinding noises
increased steering effort
and the steering column breaks
resulting in the loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Rough idle
engine stalling
check engine light comes on
power loss
engine bogging down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause the loss of vital information, such as speed, temperature, and fuel level, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Gauges (temperature
gas
speedometer
and RPM) go dead while driving
digital odometer does not register miles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition lock can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ignition lock refuses to turn with coded key
key gets stuck in ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
electrical system malfunction
smoke and flames coming from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the security/door lock system can cause the doors to unlock while driving, potentially leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Doors unlock on their own while driving
security system malfunction.
